                    oc:sectionTitle "Code Style Guidelines" ],
                [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:Paragraph ;
                            oc:blockType "paragraph" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:textContent "A user may ask you to create, edit, or analyze the contents of a .docx file. A .docx file is essentially a ZIP archive containing XML files and other resources that you can read or edit. You have different tools and workflows available for different tasks." ] ;
                    oc:sectionLevel 2 ;
                    oc:sectionOrder 1 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "Overview" ],
                [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:Paragraph ;
                            oc:blockType "paragraph" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:textContent "When editing an existing Word document, use the **Document library** (a Python library for OOXML manipulation). The library automatically handles infrastructure setup and provides methods for document manipulation. For complex scenarios, you can access the underlying DOM directly through the library." ] ;
                    oc:hasSubsection [ a oc:Section ;
                            oc:hasContent _:ref_484c124c2150b3ad,
                                [ a oc:Paragraph ;
                                    oc:blockType "paragraph" ;
                                    oc:contentOrder 2 ;
                                    oc:textContent "The Document library provides both high-level methods for common operations and direct DOM access for complex scenarios." ] ;
                            oc:sectionLevel 3 ;
                            oc:sectionOrder 1 ;
                            oc:sectionTitle "Workflow" ] ;
                    oc:sectionLevel 2 ;
                    oc:sectionOrder 5 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "Editing an existing Word document" ],
                [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:Paragraph ;
                            oc:blockType "paragraph" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 2 ;
                            oc:textContent "**Batching Strategy**: Group related changes into batches of 3-10 changes. This makes debugging manageable while maintaining efficiency. Test each batch before moving to the next." ],
                        [ a oc:Paragraph ;
                            oc:blockType "paragraph" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:textContent "This workflow allows you to plan comprehensive tracked changes using markdown before implementing them in OOXML. **CRITICAL**: For complete tracked changes, you must implement ALL changes systematically." ],
                        [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """# BAD - Replaces entire sentence
'<w:del><w:r><w:delText>The term is 30 days.</w:delText></w:r></w:del><w:ins><w:r><w:t>The term is 60 days.</w:t></w:r></w:ins>'

# GOOD - Only marks what changed, preserves original <w:r> for unchanged text
'<w:r w:rsidR="00AB12CD"><w:t>The term is </w:t></w:r><w:del><w:r><w:delText>30</w:delText></w:r></w:del><w:ins><w:r><w:t>60</w:t></w:r></w:ins><w:r w:rsidR="00AB12CD"><w:t> days.</w:t></w:r>'
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 5 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 85-91" ],
                        [ a oc:Paragraph ;
                            oc:blockType "paragraph" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 3 ;
                            oc:textContent """**Principle: Minimal, Precise Edits**
When implementing tracked changes, only mark text that actually changes. Repeating unchanged text makes edits harder to review and appears unprofessional. Break replacements into: [unchanged text] + [deletion] + [insertion] + [unchanged text]. Preserve the original run's RSID for unchanged text by extracting the `<w:r>` element from the original and reusing it.""" ],
                        [ a oc:Paragraph ;
                            oc:blockType "paragraph" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 4 ;
                            oc:textContent "Example - Changing \"30 days\" to \"60 days\" in a sentence:" ] ;
